    "body": "<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n\n## Purpose\nFlashinfer has a new allreduce API: https://github.com/flashinfer-ai/flashinfer/pull/2130\nand a `mnnvl` backend for allreduce optimized for multi-node NVLink cases (https://github.com/flashinfer-ai/flashinfer/pull/1213).\nThe `mnnvl` backend performs [same/better](https://github.com/flashinfer-ai/flashinfer/blob/d5eaa429b1c2c3cc51fe078028551fef10ca9cc9/flashinfer/comm/allreduce.py#L261-L267) than the old `trtllm` backend that vLLM currently uses.\nThe new API allows choosing between the two backends. As of flashinfer 0.6.2, when `backend` is `auto`, `mnnvl` will always be chosen.\n\nThis PR \n- ~updates the allreduce fusion pass to use the new API.~ Already done by https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/33985, but 33985 only uses `trtllm` backend.\n- Add env var to choose between backends. `VLLM_FLASHINFER_ALLREDUCE_BACKEND`: `[auto, mnnvl, trtllm]` (default `auto`)\n- Allow flashinfer allreduce to be used standalone in the absence of rmsnorm (e.g., MoE+TP). Turn on with `VLLM_ALLREDUCE_USE_FLASHINFER=1` (default 0)\n## Eval\n```\nvllm serve meta-llama/Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct  --disable-log-requests --no-enable-prefix-caching -tp4 --compilation-config.pass_config.fuse_allreduce_rms=true\nlm_eval --model local-chat-completions --tasks gsm8k --model_args model=meta-llama/Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct,base_url=http://0.0.0.0:8000/v1/chat/completions,max_gen_toks=16384,num_concurrent=64 --batch_size auto --fewshot_as_multiturn --apply_chat_template\n```\n```\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value |   |Stderr|\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|-----:|---|-----:|\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9356|±  |0.0068|\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  |0.8901|±  |0.0086|\n```\n## Benchmark\n**Server cmd:**\nBaseline (main branch, no fusion):\n```\nvllm serve meta-llama/Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct  --disable-log-requests --no-enable-prefix-caching -tp4\n```\nflashinfer\n```\nVLLM_FLASHINFER_ALLREDUCE_BACKEND=auto # set this to \"trtllm\" for existing old backend. Otherwise defaults to \"mnnvl\" backend.\nVLLM_ALLREDUCE_USE_FLASHINFER=1 # Turn this on if you need this kernel to be used as a standalone allreduce op\nvllm serve meta-llama/Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct  --disable-log-requests --no-enable-prefix-caching -tp4 --compilation-config.pass_config.fuse_allreduce_rms=true\n```\n**Client cmd**\n```\nDURATION_SECONDS=60;\nvllm bench serve \\\n   --model meta-llama/Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct \\\n   --dataset-name sonnet  \\\n   --dataset-path benchmarks/sonnet.txt \\\n   --request-rate \"$qps\" \\\n   --num-prompts $((DURATION_SECONDS * qps))\n```\n\nMean TTFT and TPOT:\n**TP4** (4xGB200) fuse enabled, mnnvl backend vs trtllm backend:\nqps | mnnvl ttft | mnnvl tpot | trtllm ttft | trtllm tpot\n-- | -- | -- | -- | --\n1 | 43.33 | 9.53 | 45.53 | 9.65\n5 | 56.41 | 10.97 | 57.46 | 10.99\n10 | 68.13 | 13.69 |  68.56 | 13.72\n\nNo TPOT slowdown in single node.\n\n**TP8** (4xGB200 per node, 2 nodes)\nmnnvl - fuse enabled, mnnvl backend\nstandalone - fusion disabled, but `VLLM_ALLREDUCE_USE_FLASHINFER=1`, mnnvl backend\nbaseline - default: fusion disabled, standalone disabled\n(Note that trtllm backend is absent in this comparison, as I run into errors when trying it with multinode)\nqps | mnnvl ttft | mnnvl tpot | standalone ttft | standalone tpot | baseline ttft | baseline tpot\n-- | -- | -- | -- | -- | -- | --\n1 | 57.8 | 8.55 | 55.33 | 9.15 | 57.31 | 10.75\n5 | 66.94 | 10.93 | 66.04 | 11.6 | 67.34 | 13.3\n10 | 88.32 | 17.24 | 84.07 | 17.66 | 84.38 | 19.45\n\n\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
